gallery.title: No. 18 Oregon State Beavers own the state with 85-79 overtime win over No. 7 Oregon Ducks

image.caption: Oregon's Erin Boley (right) has her shot blocked by Oregon State's Katie McWilliams during overtime as No. 18 Oregon State upsets the No. 7 Oregon Ducks 85-79 in overtime at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard (left) gets the loose ball from Oregon State's Taya Corosdale in overtime play as No. 18 Oregon State upsets the No. 7 Oregon Ducks 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Oregon State's Kat Tudor celebrates three of her game-high 34 points during the first half against Oregon at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Oregon's Ruthy Hebard (right) and Oregon State's Marie Gźlich battle for the ball during the first half at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon State's Kat Tudor (left) looses the ball to Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu during overtime as No. 18 Oregon State upsets No. 7 Oregon 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard scores two of her 24 total points of the night in front of Oregon State's Marie Gźlich in overtime as No. 18 Oregon State beats No. 7 Oregon 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu (right) knocks the ball from Oregon State's Marie Gźlich during the first half as No. 18 Oregon State upsets No. 7 Oregon 85-79 in overtime at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard (24) dives for the loose ball between OSU defenders Mikayla Pivec (0) and Marie Gźlich during the first half against Oregon State at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Oregon's Ruthy Hebard blocks Oregon State's Marie Gźlich during the first half at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

With time running out in overtime, Oregon State's Katie McWilliams (right) is fouled by Oregon's Maite Cazorla as No. 18 Oregon State beats No. 7 Oregon 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

From left to right, Oregon State's, Marie Gźlich, Mikayla Pivec, Taya Corosdale, and Katie McWilliams celebrate McWilliams being fouled by the Ducks in overtime as No. 18 Oregon State upsets No. 7 Oregon 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Maite Cazorla (left) and Justine Hall walk off the floor as Oregon State celebrates their 14 consecutive win over the Ducks 85-79 at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

For 14 consecutive games played, the Oregon State Beavers celebrate their 85-79 overtime win over No. 7 Oregon at Gill Coliseum in Corvallis on Friday, Jan. 19, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
